    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Copper-based glaze that shows as blushes of red, occasionally dotted with fine green spots on a pinkish-red ground. It can give the effect of blushing skin or ripening fruit. It was an innovation if the Qing dynasty at Jingdezhen, and appears most often on small ceramics.</Note_Text>
